header.gameNote: FRONTIER COMMUNICATIONS AMERICAN ATHLETIC CONFERENCE MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINAL

videos.description: Galen Robinson hits the banker as Houston takes a 13-5 lead.
videos.headline: Robinson drives for the layup

videos.description: Bertrand Nkali takes the feed and finishes with the dunk.
videos.headline: Nkali with the big dunk

videos.description: Rob Gray Jr drains the long jumper as Houston ties it at 24.
videos.headline: Gray Jr hits the contested jumper

videos.description: Rodney Purvis takes the feed and nails the 3-pointer to give UConn a 27-24 lead.
videos.headline: Purvis drains the corner 3

videos.description: Damyean Dotson hits the 3 as Houston pulls within 35-33.
videos.headline: Dotson 3-pointer cuts into UConn lead

videos.description: Amida Brimah blocks the shot on one end and then Rodney Purvis finishes with the pull up jumper.
videos.headline: UConn turns defense into offense

videos.description: Kenton Facey gets offensive rebound and scores.
videos.headline: Facey scores down low

videos.description: Jalen Adams hits a 3-pointer to give UConn a 62-55 in their win over Houston to advance to the American tournament semifinals.
videos.headline: Adams drains the clutch 3 in UConn's win

videos.description: Rodney Purvis hits the runner to give UConn a late 74-63 lead.
videos.headline: Purvis seals the deal
